\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces The localized-tadpole plane $(\Theta _{01},\Theta _{23})$. The base block sits at $\Theta _{\rm  base}=(126,-36)$ and \emph  {fails} the tadpole; the eight-anomaly witness of $27$ multiplets moves only to $(126,-20)$ and still fails; the $45$-multiplet completion (green arrow) brings the total to the origin. Anomaly freedom alone does not cancel the tadpole --- but a joint completion does.}}{9}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:tadmap}{{4}{9}{The localized-tadpole plane $(\Theta _{01},\Theta _{23})$. The base block sits at $\Theta _{\rm base}=(126,-36)$ and \emph {fails} the tadpole; the eight-anomaly witness of $27$ multiplets moves only to $(126,-20)$ and still fails; the $45$-multiplet completion (green arrow) brings the total to the origin. Anomaly freedom alone does not cancel the tadpole --- but a joint completion does}{figure.caption.8}{}}
